Implement a simple gRPC client for a Note Service that allows users to create and list notes. The service definition is provided in a `notes.proto` file. The client should be able to send a request to create a new note with a title and content, and another request to list all the existing notes. The server is assumed to be running and listening on `127.0.0.1:50050`.

The `notes.proto` file contains the following service definition:

```proto
syntax = "proto3";

package notes;

service NoteService {
  rpc CreateNote (Note) returns (NoteId);
  rpc ListNotes (Empty) returns (NoteList);
}

message Note {
  string title = 1;
  string content = 2;
}

message NoteId {
  string id = 1;
}

message NoteList {
  repeated Note notes = 1;
}

message Empty {}
```

